text.tspan: A button group by default has 8px between each button.
The last button in the group is followed by a 16px spacer
An icon button group by default has 0px between each icon button.
The last icon button in the group is followed by a 16px spacer
A filter group by default has 0px between each filter. The last filter in the
group is followed by a 16px spacer
Groups themseleves can be created with any items. Items are spaced by 16px by default and
groups are followed by a 16px spacer. All of this spacing can be customized!
Toolbar groups include a few specific types, such as button groups, icon button groups and filter
groups. Groups themseleves can be created with any items. Items are spaced by 16px by default
and groups are followed by a 16px spacer. All of this spacing can be customized!
The bulk selector is always left-aligned within the toolbar and followed
Pagination is always right-aligned in the toolbar. If the options menu and full pagination is used, there is
24px between the two. If the options menu and compact pagination are used, there is 8px between them.
The vertical divider is followed by a 16px spacer by default, and can be placed anywere within the
toolbar, although it is recommended to be used between groups if you need more differentiation
The overflow menu is used when the screen size becomes too small to incorporate many actions
in one line of the toolbar, and they collapse into a kebab.
The search filter is followed by an 8px spacer by default. It is intended to be used
in combination with a Filter Group when you want to support multiple filters within
a toolber. See Filters documentation for more information.
